{{Infobox language |name=Palor |nativename= |states=[[Senegal]] |region=[[Thies]] |ethnicity=[[Palor people|Serer-Palor]] |speakers={{sigfig|10,700|3}} |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Senegambian languages|Senegambian]] |fam4=[[Cangin languages|Cangin]] |fam5=Palor–Ndut |iso3=fap |glotto=palo1243 |glottorefname=Palor }}
'''Palor''' (Falor, Paloor) is a language spoken in [[Senegal]]. The speakers of this language - the [[Palor people]] or Serer-Palor, are ethnically [[Serer people|Serers]] but they do not speak the [[Serer language|Serer-Sine language]]. Like the [[Lehar language|Lehar]], [[Saafi language|Saafi]], [[Noon language|Noon]] and [[Ndut language|Ndut]] languages, their language is classified as one of the [[Cangin languages]] attached to the [[Niger–Congo]] family. Palor is closer to Ndut.
==Other names== Sili-Sili (the name for their language) and ''Waro'' (the name for themselves).<ref name=e18/>
