{{Infobox language |name=Yameo |nativename=Nijyamïï Nikyejaada |extinct=? |states=NE [[Peru]] |region=western Amazon |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Peba–Yaguan languages|Peba–Yaguan]] |iso3=yme |glotto=yame1242 |glottorefname=Yameo }}
'''Yameo''' is an extinct language from [[Peba–Yaguan languages|Peba–Yaguan language family]] that was formerly spoken in [[Peru]]. It was spoken along the banks of the [[Amazon River]] from the [[Tigre River]] to the [[Nanay River]].
